Google Chrome is still the most popular Internet browser, according to data from NetMarketShare for April 2018. Chrome leads both the mobile and desktop market, with over 60% market share across both platforms. Safari is the main competitor to Chrome on mobile, with a market share of 27.00% – compared to Chrome’s market share of 63.12%. Internet Explorer competes with Firefox for second place on desktop, and is currently ahead by less than 2%. The most popular Internet browsers across mobile and desktop for April 2018 are listed below.  